tself stylistically as silence, stuttering, fragmentation, and encoding. Mining archives of unpublished documents, including manuscripts, diaries, and letters, where authors were more candid, as well as rereading the work of both major and minor figures, a number of whom were subject to prison sentences, Five Long Winters offers a new way of approaching the literature of the Romantic era.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 23. Jul 2020) 0aAuthors, Englishy18th centuryxPolitical and social views. 0aEnglish literaturey18th centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aPolitics and literaturezEnglandxHistoryy18th century. 0aRomanticismzEngland. 4aColeridge. 4aFlower. 4aGodwin. 4aRomanticism. 4aThelwall. 4aWollstonecraft. 4aWordsworth. 4asedition. 4atreason. 4atrial. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / English, Irish, Scottish, Welsh.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUP Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311070420440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780804787307zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780804787307423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780804787307.jpg  a978-3-11-070420-4  SUP Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles